'''快閃店'''是商家开设的短期[[销售|销售]]場所，通常這些[[销售|销售]]場所開設数天至数周后後就會關閉，有時主辦方在舉辦某些活動時會出現快閃店，活動結束後快閃店也會同步關閉。快閃店的雛形可以追溯到1298年的維也納<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.austria.info/uk/things-to-do/skiing-and-winter/christmas-markets/christmas-markets-in-vienna|title=Christmas markets in Vienna|publisher=Austrian National Tourist Office|access-date=2 April 2017|archive-date=2019-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191010124422/https://www.austria.info/uk/things-to-do/skiing-and-winter/christmas-markets/christmas-markets-in-vienna|dead-url=no}}</ref>以及稍晚出現的歐洲[[聖誕市場|聖誕市場]]。現代快閃店从1997年的美國洛杉矶开始，逐步傳播至美国全國、加拿大<ref name="halloween">{{Cite news|first=Sean|author=Gregory|title=Why Pop-Up Shops Are Hot|url=http://www.time.com/time/business/article/0,8599,1935030,00.html|quote=Ricky's Costume Superstore in New York City was ready for Halloween|work=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]|date=November 6, 2009|accessdate=November 22, 2009|archive-date=2012-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104120624/http://www.time.com/time/business/article/0,8599,1935030,00.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|first=Stephanie|author=Clifford|title=Hanging Out at a Mall for the Holidays|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/30/business/media/30adco.html?_r=1|quote=The Haute Spot is a so-called pop-up concept, meaning that the store is not permanent. The location will be open Nov. 28 through Dec. 26.|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=October 30, 2008|accessdate=November 22, 2009|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608175120/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/30/business/media/30adco.html?_r=1|dead-url=no}}</ref>、中国<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-08-23/why-nutella-and-nike-have-hong-kong-shoppers-lining-up-for-hours/|title=Why Nutella and Nike Have Hong Kong Shoppers Lining Up For Hours|first=Daniela|author=Wei|date=August 23, 2016|work=[[Daybreak_Asia|Daybreak Asia]]|publisher=[[Bloomberg_L.P.|Bloomberg]]|location=Hong Kong|accessdate=November 30, 2016|archive-date=2016-08-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827071116/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-08-23/why-nutella-and-nike-have-hong-kong-shoppers-lining-up-for-hours|dead-url=no}}</ref>、日本<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://hypebeast.com/2016/10/stanton-street-sports-japan-pop-up-store|title=Stanton Street Sports Heads Overseas for a Pop-up Store in Japan|first=Mallory|author=Chin|date=October 26, 2016|publisher=Hypebeast|location=New York|accessdate=November 30, 2016|archive-date=2018-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180921051702/https://hypebeast.com/2016/10/stanton-street-sports-japan-pop-up-store|dead-url=no}}</ref>、墨西哥<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.admexico.mx/estilo-de-vida/agenda/articulos/pop-up-store-compra-moda-nacional-reforma-222/337|title=Pop Up Store 2014|first=Fernanda|author=Lascurain|date=August 13, 2014|publisher=[[Architectural_Digest|Architectural Digest]]|location=Mexico City|accessdate=November 30, 2016|archive-date=2018-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613210647/http://www.admexico.mx/estilo-de-vida/agenda/articulos/pop-up-store-compra-moda-nacional-reforma-222/337|dead-url=no}}</ref>、法国<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.highsnobiety.com/2016/06/26/kanye-west-shop-paris-street-style/|title=Here’s What People Wore to Kanye West’s Pop-Up Shop in Paris|first=Brock|author=Cardiner|date=June 26, 2016|publisher=[[High_Snobiety|High Snobiety]]|location=Paris|accessdate=November 30, 2016|archive-date=2018-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181003154757/https://www.highsnobiety.com/2016/06/26/kanye-west-shop-paris-street-style/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、德国<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://retaildesignblog.net/2016/06/28/samsung-pop-up-store-by-cheil-germany-frankfurt-germany/|title=Samsung pop-up store by Cheil Germany, Frankfurt – Germany|date=June 28, 2016|publisher=[[Retail_Design_Blog|Retail Design Blog]]|location=Germany|accessdate=November 30, 2016|archive-date=20